'''Korriban: Planet of Lost Souls''' is a [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying]] supplement written by [[Cory J. Herndon]] and published on [[Wizards.com]] by [[Wizards of the Coast]] in [[October]] [[2003]]. Part of the ''[[Planet Hoppers]]'' series, it was published in five parts, released one week at a time, and tells the story of the doomed voyage of the [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] vessel ''[[Jynni's Virtue]]'' to the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] tomb world of [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]].

==Contents==
===Part 1: Haunted Hideout===
''&hellip;a [[Naz Felyood|pirate captain]] mistakes a [[Korriban/Legends|dead world]] saturated in the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|Dark Side]] for the perfect place to lay low.''<ref name="Korriban" />

===Part 2: Valley of Darkness===
''&hellip;[[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] [[Captain/Legends|captain]] Felyood does a little [[Burial/Legends|tomb]] raiding among the crypts of the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lords]].''<ref name="Korriban" />

===Part 3: The Dark Lord's Heart===
''&hellip;a treasure-hunting pirate finds a [[Heart of Graush|deadly artifact]] that changes his life forever.''<ref name="Korriban" />

===Part 4: The Sith Shall Rise Again===
''&hellip;a shipwrecked crew try to save themselves and [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] from the awakening [[Sith/Legends|Sith]].''<ref name="Korriban" />

===Part 5: Sole Survivor===
''&hellip;an unfortunate treasure hunter learns what happens to those left behind on Korriban.''<ref name="Korriban" />

